  "base_commit": "216641169f3b51a5bdc04c764f0436b65edc3cf8",
  "pr_number": 8061,
  "issue_number": 6710,
  "issue_title": "A graphs start node is its own Immediate-Dominator in your implementation which should not be the case",
  "issue_body": "The function immediate_dominators currently returns a result where the start node is its own idom.\r\nBy definition the starting node of a graph is the only node without any immediate dominator.\r\n\r\nMaybe i am wrong but it would be nice if your could change the behaviour of this function to be according to the definition of i-dom.\r\n\"Every node, except the entry node, has an immediate dominator.\" [Quote from wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dominator_(graph_theory)) with reference to [Reference](https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/357062.357071)",
  "merged_at": "2025-10-28T23:44:55Z",
  "test_cmd": [
